Quid ait, &a Hitherto we have seen Antiphila’s manner of life in her lover’s absence, and that it had been agreeable to the stiictast rules of innocence and decency. It now remains, that we be informed how she stood affected to Clinia; and whether her, attachment here was still the same as formerly. This Syrus makes appear by her manner of behaving when hewas named to her, and so makes good what he had advanced to Clinia in the beginning, vs. 24. — 64.
